<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis box="[214,307,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Remarks</emphasis>
:In total 
<number box="[397,424,644,668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="24.0">24</number>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber" authorityName="Fieber" box="[657,822,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Fieber">
<emphasis box="[657,747,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Chlorita</emphasis>
Fieber
</taxonomicName>
are known from the Palaeartic region. Four of them: 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribaut, 1933" authorityName="Ribaut" authorityYear="1933" box="[516,812,673,697]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subulata">
<emphasis box="[516,642,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. subulata</emphasis>
(Ribaut, 
<number box="[748,804,673,697]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1933.0">1933</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1806" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.bestMatchDistance="81" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis box="[827,946,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. viridula</emphasis>
(Fallen, 
<number box="[153,209,702,727]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1806.0">1806</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1959" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1959" box="[228,516,703,727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamaninii">
<emphasis box="[228,360,703,727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. tamaninii</emphasis>
Wagner, 
<number box="[462,516,703,727]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ossiannilsson, 1939" authorityName="Ossiannilsson" authorityYear="1939" box="[565,895,702,727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paolii">
<emphasis box="[565,658,702,727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. paolii</emphasis>
(Ossiannilsson, 
<number box="[833,887,702,727]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1939.0">1939</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
belong to the 
<taxonomicName box="[153,335,732,756]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis box="[153,335,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Chlorita viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and are closely related. Wagner (
<number box="[846,901,732,756]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1959.0">1959</number>
) published a key to distinguish the above-mentioned species. Up to now, in Switzerland only 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.bestMatchDistance="29" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ribaut 
<number box="[332,388,791,815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1933.0">1933</number>
, Cerutti 
<number box="[481,535,790,815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1939.0">1939</number>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Trivellone &amp;Pollini Paltrinieri 2011" authorityName="Trivellone &amp;Pollini Paltrinieri" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paolii">
<emphasis box="[596,690,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. paolii</emphasis>
(Trivellone &amp;Pollini Paltrinieri 
<number box="[153,207,820,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
were recorded. In 
<number box="[417,472,820,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2011.0">2011</number>
, the first author had collected specimens with aedeagus morphological characteristics quite different from 
<taxonomicName box="[756,875,849,873]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.bestMatchDistance="69" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis box="[756,875,849,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1031,849,873]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paolii">
<emphasis box="[934,1031,849,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. paolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to the key after Wagner (
<number box="[557,613,878,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1959.0">1959</number>
), two main subgroups of species were recognized based on the characteristics of the appendages of the aedeagus: appendages without ablunt tooth and convergent in the 
<emphasis box="[690,875,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">viridula-subulata</emphasis>
subgroup; and appendages with ablunt tooth and divergent in the 
<emphasis box="[703,876,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">paolii-tamaninii</emphasis>
subgroup. The appendages of the examined specimens do neither coincide perfectly with the first, nor with the second subgroup. The following description of aspecimen is proposed as reference to further collections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis box="[214,369,1085,1108]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Determination</emphasis>
:The genital plate with parameres and the appendices of the anal tube are illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[437,502,1113,1137]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="6.[138,170,1098,1118]" captionTargetBox="[138,1022,123,1081]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[138,1023,518,1083]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Chlorita cf. tamaninii Wagner, 1959: A – genital plates, valve and styles dorsally; B – styles laterally; C – aedeagus laterally; D – view of aedeagus from above. (photos: P. Scaramozzino &amp; V. Trivellone)." pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Figs 
<number box="[489,502,1114,1137]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A and 
<number box="[574,588,1114,1137]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
B, respectively; they are similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chlorita" genus.bestMatchDistance="191" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after Le Quesne &amp;Payne (
<number box="[481,538,1142,1167]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1981.0">1981</number>
). In the male, aedeagus with apair of recurved appendages, longer than main stem, without tooth along outer margin; but hardly S-shaped in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[416,480,1201,1225]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="6.[138,170,1098,1118]" captionTargetBox="[138,1022,123,1081]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[138,1023,518,1083]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Chlorita cf. tamaninii Wagner, 1959: A – genital plates, valve and styles dorsally; B – styles laterally; C – aedeagus laterally; D – view of aedeagus from above. (photos: P. Scaramozzino &amp; V. Trivellone)." pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[466,480,1201,1225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[480,498,1201,1225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">C</collectionCode>
) and ending in sharp-hooked apices (
<figureCitation box="[902,967,1201,1225]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="6.[138,170,1098,1118]" captionTargetBox="[138,1022,123,1081]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[138,1023,518,1083]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Chlorita cf. tamaninii Wagner, 1959: A – genital plates, valve and styles dorsally; B – styles laterally; C – aedeagus laterally; D – view of aedeagus from above. (photos: P. Scaramozzino &amp; V. Trivellone)." pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[952,967,1201,1225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[967,988,1201,1225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">D</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
